---
import CalculatorPage from '../../components/CalculatorPage.astro';
import DistanceCalculator from '../../components/DistanceCalculator.astro';
import { socialImages } from '../../data/social';
---

<CalculatorPage
  title="Decibel distance calculator | dBcheck"
  description="Estimate how a sound level may change with distance from an ideal point source under simplified free-field conditions."
  kicker="Decibel Distance Calculator"
  heading="Distance changes level, but the room changes the rule."
  intro="Estimate the idealized level change between two distances while keeping real-world reflections, barriers and source behavior in view."
  socialImage={socialImages.fundamentals}
>
  <DistanceCalculator />

  <Fragment slot="references">
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">How it works</span>
      <h2>Spherical spreading</h2>
      <p>An ideal point source in a free field loses about 6 dB each time distance doubles. The calculation uses the ratio between the two entered distances.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">Model boundary</span>
      <h2>Real places are not free fields</h2>
      <p>Walls, floors, terrain, barriers and source directivity alter propagation. A line source can follow a different distance relationship.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">Reference</span>
      <h2>Use the result as a comparison</h2>
      <p>The <a href="https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/ENVIRonment/noise/measurement/handbook.cfm">FHWA measurement handbook</a> describes the free-field point-source assumption and its limits.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</CalculatorPage>
